UNITED STATES of America v. William Garfield JOHNSON. No. 7998. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 14, 1935. Carl C. Donaugh, U. S. Atty., and Edwin D. Hicks, Asst. U. S. Ally., both, of Portland, Or. Chas. W. Erskine, of Portland, Or., for appellee.

' Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered, appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
